Here’s a Python example using Flask to provide immediate feedback to participants after they submit experiment data:
python
from flask import Flask, request, jsonify

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/submit_data', methods=['POST'])
def submit_data():
    participant_data = request.json
    # Process participant data (e.g., store in database)
    feedback = {
        "participant_id": participant_data.get("id"),
        "feedback": "Thank you! Your data has been received and will be analyzed by our research team."
    }
    return jsonify(feedback)

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run()

This snippet shows how to handle participant submissions and return immediate feedback after data collection.
